stylometry: There is always a trade-off when making business decisions. If you want your business to have a high level of customer service, then youre going to have to have more employees on hand, which in turn makes payroll higher, and ultimately your prices of your products will have to increase and be higher and more expensive. If you are like Walmart and have every day extremely low prices, then your customer service is going to suffer. If there is a high demand for a product, then the price is going to go up because the public wants it and the supply is not going to be too high. If the demand is low, then we want the price of the product to be low also because it that means we have a huge supply of it, and customers are not fighting over it. The higher the elasticity, the more substitutes there are avalable. Management needs to find the best price for the product that will satisfy the needs specifically for their business and prove to be the most effective and efficient.
